databricks:index/mwsCustomerManagedKeys:.description:
{{% examples %}}
## Example Usage

> **Note** If you've used the resource before, please add `use_cases = ["MANAGED_SERVICES"]` to keep the previous behaviour.
{{% example %}}
### Customer-managed key for managed services

You must configure this during workspace creation

```typescript
import * as pulumi from "@pulumi/pulumi";
import * as aws from "@pulumi/aws";
import * as databricks from "@pulumi/databricks";

const config = new pulumi.Config();
const databricksAccountId = config.requireObject("databricksAccountId");
const current = aws.getCallerIdentity({});
const databricksManagedServicesCmk = current.then(current => aws.iam.getPolicyDocument({
    version: "2012-10-17",
    statements: [
        {
            sid: "Enable IAM User Permissions",
            effect: "Allow",
            principals: [{
                type: "AWS",
                identifiers: [current.accountId],
            }],
            actions: ["kms:*"],
            resources: ["*"],
        },
        {
            sid: "Allow Databricks to use KMS key for control plane managed services",
            effect: "Allow",
            principals: [{
                type: "AWS",
                identifiers: ["arn:aws:iam::414351767826:root"],
            }],
            actions: [
                "kms:Encrypt",
                "kms:Decrypt",
            ],
            resources: ["*"],
        },
    ],
}));
